CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper August 16, 1947, pg. 27, reads: "Co-Workers Entertained - Miss Marjorie E. Gaines of Highland View Heights entertained some of her co-workers of the Veterans Administration at the Hermitage Street home of her grandmother, Mrs. Nannie B. Allen, last Saturday. The guests were Miss Estelle Van Duyer of California, Ruth Crouse of Ingram, Bessie Wiess of McKeesport and Helen Papariella of Pittsburgh. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Veterans Administration workers Estelle Van Duyer, Ruth Crouse, Bessie Wiess, Helen Papariella and Marjorie E. Gaines gathered on porch of home of Nannie B. Allen, Hermitage Street
